LineComment.Text: ************************************************************************* ** This function calculates the calendar week for the current CPU date ** ** ------------------------------------------------------------------- ** ** The calendar week is the return value of the function. ** ** The week number is calculated according to DIN 1355 / ISO 8601. ** ** "Week no. 1 is the first week, which includes at least four days ** ** of the new year. The beginning of a week is always a Monday." ** ** ** ** The function can be used from year 1991 to 2089. ** ** ** *************************************************************************
Calculate year including century and days passed since Jan 1 1990 upto Jan 1 current year
Calculate which day of the week current year started on
Correction when week number equals 0 - Check which week was the last in previous year.
A year usually start and ends on the same weekday, but not on leap years.
If the previous year starts or ends on a Thursday it has 53 weeks.
A year usually start and ends on the same weekday, but not on leap years.
Number of weeks current year; if first or last day is thursday then the year has 53 weeks otherwise only 52
If estimated week number is greater than maximum of current year, it must be the first week of next year
